items.name: Jessica Alba
items.description:
This embedding (textual inversion) has been trained after carefully selecting 30 images . All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them. I hope you like it!.

As with many embeddings, just play with weights to get better results when needed.

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review (after having tested the model) would be highly appreciated or at least press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

Jessica Marie Alba (born April 28, 1981)[2] is an American actress and businesswoman. She began her television and film appearances at age 13 in Camp Nowhere and The Secret World of Alex Mack (1994), and rose to prominence at age 19 as the lead actress of the television series Dark Angel (2000‚Äì2002), for which she received a Golden Globe nomination.

Her big screen breakthrough came in Honey (2003). She soon established herself as a Hollywood actress, and has starred in numerous box office hits throughout her career, including Fantastic Four (2005), Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer (2007), Good Luck Chuck (2007), The Eye (2008), Valentine's Day (2010), Little Fockers (2010), and Mechanic: Resurrection (2016). She is a frequent collaborator of director Robert Rodriguez, having starred in Sin City (2005), Machete (2010), Spy Kids: All the Time in the World (2011), Machete Kills (2013), and Sin City: A Dame to Kill For (2014). From 2019 to 2020, Alba starred in the Spectrum action crime series L.A.'s Finest.

In 2011, Alba co-founded The Honest Company, a consumer goods company that sells baby, personal and household products.[10] Magazines including Men's Health, Vanity Fair and FHM have included her on their lists of the world's most beautiful women.

items.name: Invisible, Inc. Style
items.description:
Inspired by 1to3fall5's Don't Starve Together LoRA, this LoRA attempts to generate the style of Invisible Inc. on portraits.

It seems to work fairly well with SDXL Base with few Refiner steps (I did 24:1) at strength 0.9. It does like to duplicate lapels, and at some aspect ratios has a tendency to either duplicate mouths/noses or add subjects, though this is usually easy to correct by changing the aspect ratio. It has very limited ability to generate objects in the style beyond clothing and faces.

Data collected from Invisible, Inc. Wiki.

Deepika Padukone (born 5 January 1986) is an Indian actress who works predominantly in Hindi films. One of the highest-paid actresses in India, her accolades include three Filmfare Awards. She features in listings of the nation's most popular personalities; Time named her one of the 100 most influential people in the world in 2018 and awarded her the TIME100 Impact Award in 2022.

Padukone, the daughter of the badminton player Prakash Padukone, was born in Copenhagen and raised in Bangalore. As a teenager, she played badminton in national level championships but left her career in the sport to become a fashion model. She soon received offers for film roles and made her acting debut in 2006 as the title character of the Kannada film Aishwarya. Padukone then played a dual role opposite Shah Rukh Khan in her first Bollywood release, the romance Om Shanti Om (2007), which won her the Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut. Padukone received praise for her starring role in the romance Love Aaj Kal (2009), but this was followed by a brief setback.

The romantic comedy Cocktail (2012) marked a turning point in her career, and she gained further success with starring roles in the romantic comedies Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani and Chennai Express (both 2013), the heist comedy Happy New Year (2014), Sanjay Leela Bhansali's period dramas Bajirao Mastani (2015) and Padmaavat (2018), and the Hollywood action film XXX: Return of Xander Cage (2017). She also received critical acclaim for playing a character based on Juliet in Bhansali's tragic romance Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela (2013) and a headstrong daughter in the comedy-drama Piku (2015), winning two Filmfare Awards for Best Actress. Following a short hiatus and two commercially unsuccessful productions under her own company Ka Productions, Padukone starred in her highest-grossing Indian film, Pathaan (2023).

items.name: Zeitgeist - Ghibli (Character and Style LoRa's for SDXL)
items.description:
See here for an extensive article about my entire training workflow and configuration if you want to train your own SDXL 1.0 LoRa's and achieve results similar as me!

Recommended weight: 1.0 - or lower when you combine it with other LoRa's

Recommended model and VAE: SDXL 1.0 with 0.9 vae

Recommended settings: 35 steps | DPM++ 2M Karras | CFG 7

Recommended negative prompt: text, watermark, signature, abstract, burned, instagram, low-quality, low-res, action figure, child drawing, jpeg, low contrast, glossy, puppet, clich√©, stock photo, magazine cover

Description

A LoRa for SDXL 1.0 based on the artstyle and some of the characters of primarily the 1980s-early 2000s Japanese animated movies by Studio Ghibli. The character LoRa's work very well to reproduce the characters in their native artstyles, but may have trouble with outfit and style flexibility due to dataset limitations.

The sample images for the characters portrayed in the Ghibli artstyle were done using both the character LoRa at 1.0 strength and the Ghibli artstyle LoRa at 0.6 strength.

Trigger words

  • Artstyle: "ghst artstyle"

  • San: "s with r hairstyle wearing w outfit"

    • with fur coat

    • with crystal necklace

    • with teeth necklace

  • Kiki: "v with f hairstyle wearing h outfit"

  • Nausica√§: "ncpp with srhh hairstyle wearing bmcc outfit"

Further usage notes

For the character LoRa's it can help sometimes to negative prompt "anime, cartoon" to force a different artstyle. It can also help to add to the positive prompt words like "dslr" for photo prompts or "realistic" for realistic digital art.

If you notice a lack of outfit likeness, emphasizing that part of the prompt can help, too. Example:

"full-length full-body screencap in ghst artstyle of (ncpp with srhh hairstyle wearing bmcc outfit:1.3)"

Generally the characters do really well at portraying the characters in their native artstyles and in their native outfits, but it can struggle a lot with portraying them in different artstyles or outfits. Unfortunately that is hard to overcome through training because of limited datasets.

Changelog

v2.0 (Nausica√§ character)

  • much reduced overtraining, much improved flexibility and diversity, at the cost of some likeness

v2.0 (Ghibli artstyle)

  • much reduced overtraining, much improved flexibility and diversity, at the cost of some likeness

v1.0

  • Initial release

Additional Info

Credit is not mandatory but I would still appreciate credit when posting images using these LoRa's on social media! Feel free to @ my Twitter and/or Instagram accounts too (@ai_characters)! I would love to know when it is used!

I share all of my model's and training knowledge for free, but donations to my Ko-Fi would be greatly appreciated! Testing so much and training so many model's costs a lot of money (and time).

Feel free to also try out my RVC2 AI voice models which you can find here!

Stats (v2.0)

Dataset:

  • Ghibli artstyle: 131x screencap

  • Nausica√§: 17x screencap, 3x fanart, 9x cosplay photo

Epochs chosen for the final models:

  • Ghibli artstyle: 10

  • Nausica√§: 24

Learning rate:

  • 3e-5 (Ghibli artstyle)

  • 8e-5 (Characters)

For the configuration used to train this model see my guide which I linked in the beginning of this post.

Stats (v1.0)

Datasets:

  • San: 23x screencap, 3x cosplay photo, 7x fanart

  • Kiki: 26x screencap, 3x cosplay photo, 3x fanart

Epochs chosen for the final models:

items.description:
Hi guys, this is my SD XL LoRA trained with paintings from the argentinian artist Julio Le Parc

https://julio-le-parc.com/

I¬¥ve come to find that there are very few SD models and LoRAs for geometric abstractions so I decided to train my own. Geometric abstractions are quite hard for generative models to develope correctly because of the organic nature of noise diffusion and I¬¥m still trying to get the best results out of this one. This is just the the first generation but I¬¥m gonna keep updating the model to make it even better.

Julio Le Parc is a very famous argentinian painter that went through many different geometric abstraction styles along his carreer. The model is trained with almost all of his work, I only left out his very earliest naturalist paintings.

Hope you like my work and you can follow me on instagram to see the training process and all my other latin american artist trained SD models and LoRAs.

https://www.instagram.com/nicolasmariar/

This model produces, like the name suggests, a little bit of everything. It's cartoonish-realism style creates everything from super cutesy to demonically horrifying.

How to use recommendations:

- Dimensions: 768x512 or 512x768

- Positive Prompt: High quality, 4k,

- Negative Prompt: I recommend Bad Dream and FastNegativeV2 negative embeds for more cartoonish generations, or Unrealistic Dream and FastNegativeV2 for more realistic generations.

- Normally this model does pretty well with faces without help or prompting, however if you run into specific face issues, aDetailer is an easy way to bring quality back to faces.

- VAE: I did not bake a vae into this model, but I used Yozora (kl-f8-anime2) vae for all the pictures for the model.

- Clip Skip, Sampling Methods, Sampling Steps, CFG Scale: Please refer to the pictures posted with the model near the end, those show ranges and how they affect the creations of this model. Wide range though, play around!

items.name: Scene - Mother holding Baby
items.description:
A young mother with her child. An image that reminds us of the beauty of life.

Trigger word is: BFMother
Additional words that may help: 1baby, mother holding baby, mother and baby, motherly, sofa, living room
Recommended Strength: 0.6 - 0.9 (I prefer 0.8)
Recommended Strength of Other Mixed LoRA / LyCORIS: 0.4 - 0.6

This originally was going to be the 3rd NSFW model I was going to work on, but it ended up being better as a SFW model to just show a mother and her child. However, the trigger tag BFMother (for breastfeeding mother) was used in training so apologies for the strange tag associated with this one. I still really like the wholesome feel to the images generated and I hope you like the positive outlook to the final outcome as well!
Note: The baby becomes extremely deformed when you try to prompt for its original purpose...
